How can we modify the addTwo(x, y) function to handle negative numbers and decimal numbers with precision up to two decimal places? Can you provide a code snippet and mathematical formula for the modified function?
Here is a possible solution:
function addTwo(x, y) {
  if (isNaN(x) || isNaN(y)) {
    return NaN;
  } else if (x < 0 && y < 0) {
    return -1 * (Math.abs(x) + Math.abs(y));
  } else {
    return (Math.round((x + y) * 100) / 100);
  }
}
The Math.round() method is used to round the result to two decimal places. To handle negative numbers, we use the Math.abs() method to get the absolute value and then multiply by -1 to get the negative sum.

